The leadership of the Azerbaijan SSR saw a succession of prominent figures, each steering the republic through different phases of Soviet history. While the specific titles varied over time, reflecting shifts in Soviet administrative nomenclature, these individuals held significant power within the republic's party and state apparatus.

*   [Sergey Kirov](/Sergei_Kirov) (1921–1926)
*   [Levon Mirzoyan](/Levon_Mirzoyan) (1926–1929)
*   [Ruhulla Akhundov](/Ruhulla_Akhundov) (1925–1926)
*   [Mir Jafar Baghirov](/Mir_Jafar_Baghirov) (1933–1953)
*   [Imam Mustafayev](/Imam_Mustafayev) (1954–1959)
*   [Veli Akhundov](/Veli_Akhundov) (1959–1969)
*   [Heydar Aliyev](/Heydar_Aliyev) (1969–1982)
*   [Kamran Baghirov](/Kamran_Baghirov) (1982–1988)
